4 2. "Superintendent" or "superintendent of schools" means the
5 executive officer of the board of education and the administrative
6 head of the school system of a district maintaining an accredited
7 school, provided the person holds an administrator's certificate
8 recognized by the State Board of Education;
9 3. "Principal" means any person other than a district
10 superintendent of schools having supervisory or administrative
11 authority over any school or school building having two or more
12 teachers. A teaching principal shall be a principal who devotes at
13 least one-half (1/2) the time school is in session to classroom
14 teaching. Teaching principals shall be required to hold
15 administrative certificates;
16 4. "Teachers" means, for purposes of complying with the State
17 Aid Law and other statutes, but not any other provision of law,
18 which apportion money on the basis of teaching units or the number
19 of teachers employed or qualified, all persons holding proper
20 certificates and connected in any capacity with the instruction of
21 pupils;
22 5. "Inductee" means any certified teacher who is employed in a
23 local school to serve as a classroom teacher under the guidance and
24 assistance of a mentor teacher or teachers;
